Cut the @onion{1} in half through the root, peel and chop into roughly 1cm pieces. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{2} (or use a #garlic press{} if you have one). Remove the core from the @red pepper{1}, cut into slices about 1cm wide and then chop into 1cm cubes. Cut the top and bottom off the @carrot{1}, peel and cut into strips lengthways, then chop into ½cm pieces (if you can get them that small!). Pull the @mint{1/4 bunch} leaves off their stalks (discard the stalks) and chop the leaves as finely as you can.

Put a large #frying pan{} on medium heat with a splash of oil and add your onion. Cook for ~{5%minutes} until soft, then add your pepper and carrot. Cook for another ~{5%minutes} then add three-quarters of your garlic. Cook for another ~{1%minute} then add the @red split lentils{50%g} and @chopped tomatoes{1%400g can}. Refill the tin(s) three-quarters with water and add that in too.

Stir in the @vegetable stock pot{1} making sure it has dissolved, then leave your bolognaise to simmer for ~{10-15%minutes} until your sauce has reduced and your lentils are soft.

> Remember to stir from time to time to stop it catching!

Once cooked, remove from the heat and pop a lid on. Leave to the side until everything else is ready.

== Minty Pesto ==

Put a large #pot{} of water on to boil with a good pinch of @salt{}. Put another frying pan on medium heat and add the @pistachios{25%g}. Dry-fry for ~{3%minutes} then remove to a #chopping board{} (don't wash the pan, we'll use it later). Chop your pistachios leaving some large and some small pieces.

> Alternatively pop them in a freezer bag and bash them with a frying pan or a rolling pin, but make sure they have cooled down first!

Put your pistachios in a #bowl{} and add your mint and the @hard Italian style cheese{40%g}(grated). Pour in the @olive oil{2%tbsp}, a pinch of salt, a good grind of @black pepper{} and mix everything together. Your minty pesto is ready!

== Pasta and Mushrooms ==

Add a good splash of oil to the now empty frying pan on medium heat, once hot, add the @button mushrooms{1}(sliced) along a good pinch of salt and a grind of black pepper. Cook for ~{8%minutes}, stirring occasionally until your mushrooms are slightly brown, then add your remaining garlic and cook for ~{30%seconds}. Meanwhile, put the @wholewheat tagliatelle{250%g} in the pot of boiling water and cook for ~{6-7%minutes} until 'al dente'.

> 'Al dente' simply means the pasta is cooked through but has a tiny bit of firmness left in the middle.

When your pasta is cooked, drain it in a #colander{}.

Once your mushrooms are brown and your garlic has cooked for ~{30%seconds}, remove from the heat and stir in half your minty pesto.

> The hard Italian cheese in the pesto will melt slightly.

Serve your pasta in #bowls{} with your bolognaise, your mushrooms and a spoonful of your remaining pesto. Enjoy!

> This veggie 'bolognaise' recipe will pack in 5 of your 5 a day!